<item>
            <title>[LU-12489] Tests marked slow that are not slow (anymore?)</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-12489</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Looking at the &quot;slow&quot; tests I definitely see soem that are no longer slow due to improvements and whatnot.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;replay-ost-single tests 8a and 8b marked as slow for zfs with citet time of 30 and 12 minutes, in my testing take 38 and 60 seconds.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;ost-pools test 23b - only takes60 seconds in my testing both zfs and ldiskfs. test 18 is listed as up to 9 minutes which is not all that long after all?&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;replay-single test 44b - I am not even sure why it&apos;s on the SLOW list, it takes 12 seconds on my system and I don&apos;t see why it would take any longer looking at the test code itself. Also considering it&apos;s the only slow test in replay-single that itself takes 2-2.5 hours to run, even if it really did take 7 minutes, that&apos;s a tiny increment to disable. There are certainly much longer tests in that script.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;sanity-quota test 61 - appears to be failing 100% for me so I am not sure how long it takes when it works, but fails rather quickly today it appears?&lt;/p&gt;</description>
